<HEAD>Train Burns In Tunnel; One Dead, 20 Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ORVIETO, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A train stalled in a tunnel after catching fire and one man suffocated while 20 other passengers were treated for smoke inhalation, railroad officials reported. They said the train was en route to <LOCATION> Bolzano </LOCATION> from <LOCATION> Rome </LOCATION> and was carrying more than 150 passengers when the incident occurred Monday. The officials said the cause of the fire has not been determined. Area residents alerted authorities when they saw smoke pouring from the tunnel. Officials said <PERSON> Romeo </PERSON> <PERSON> Ascioni </PERSON>, 64, of <LOCATION> Rome </LOCATION>, died of suffocation.
