<HEAD>Sex Charges Against Teacher Prompt Changes At School For Deaf and
Blind</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. AUGUSTINE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The only state-supported school in <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> for the deaf and blind has tightened its hiring procedures as a result of sex charges brought by male students against a former dormitory teacher. The <ORGANIZATION> Florida </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION> for the Deaf and <PERSON> Blind </PERSON>, whose alumni include musician <PERSON> Ray </PERSON> <PERSON> Charles </PERSON>, now requires six, instead of three, references from prospective employees and includes more questions on job applications about contact with children. In addition, non-teaching staffers must undergo fingerprint and criminal background checks. All new <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> teachers, including those at the <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Augustine </LOCATION> school, must already undergo such checks to be certified. Dormitory teacher <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> Johnston </PERSON>, 22, was fired in April when he was charged with sexually molesting 17 of the boys he was entrusted to protect. <PERSON> Johnston </PERSON>, hired in 1985, pleaded innocent and is being held without bail in the <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Johns </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jail </LOCATION> pending a September trial. His accusers include 19 deaf boys aged 9 to 14 who are students at the school founded in 1885. Most of the 550 students at the school are deaf and live on campus. `` There has been an enormous shock because the individual alleged to have done this is a person -LRB- who -RRB- had earned the trust of many kids, parents,'' Principal <PERSON> Kenneth </PERSON> <PERSON> D. </PERSON> <PERSON> Randall </PERSON> said in an interview published in Monday's editions of The <ORGANIZATION> Tampa </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tribune </ORGANIZATION>. As a dormitory teacher, <PERSON> Johnston </PERSON> looked after the boys and taught them how to dress, clean and study. He also supervised them in games. <PERSON> Johnston </PERS