<HEAD>Old Faithful Yellowstone's Biggest Attraction</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Yellowstone Fire Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>YELLOWSTONE NATIONAL PARK, Wyo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Old Faithful Geyser, shooting water hotter than 200 degrees as high as 184 feet in the air, is <ORGANIZATION> Yellowstone </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Park </ORGANIZATION>'s most popular tourist attraction and often is considered the symbol of the country's national park system. The geyser is about 10 miles east of the 5,500-acre `` North Fork'' fire, and firefighters are trying to help wind turn the blaze from the area. While the geyser, one of more than 200 in <LOCATION> Yellowstone </LOCATION>, is not the most powerful in the park, it is the best-known, attracting 78 percent of the park's visitors as it erupts 21 to 23 times a day at intervals from 33 minutes to more than two hours. The geyser was discovered by an exploring party in 1870, two years before the park was established by <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>. A geyser is a hot spring from which water and steam are ejected periodically. The eruptions are caused by the contact between ground water and rock that is hot enough to create steam. The Old Faithful Inn, built in 1904, was the first building in the area, which now has three lodges, including one for use during the winter. The inn, placed on the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> the </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Interior </ORGANIZATION>'s list of national historic landmarks in 1987, was expanded in 1913 and 1927 to provide 324 rooms. Other accommodations at the site include the Old Faithful Lodge cabins, providing 132 rooms, and the Old Faithful Snow Lodge, which remains open in winter, with 65 rooms. Old Faithful is the one of two areas of the park open for winter users who reach the area on cross-country skis or by snowmobile. Mammoth Hot Springs is also open in winter. Other services at Old Faithful include a general store and two service stations, one of which remains open in the winter. There are no campgrounds in the area.
