<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Israeli troops fatally shot a 13-year-old Palestinian girl and wounded three youths during fighting Tuesday in occupied <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>, Arab hospital officials reported. The army confirmed the girl's death but said it had not determined the cause. Defense Minister <PERSON> Yitzhak </PERSON> <PERSON> Rabin </PERSON> toured a detention center in <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> and vowed to quell the eight-month old <LOCATION> Palestinian </LOCATION> uprising in the occupied <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION>. `` We do n't accept the present level of violence,'' <PERSON> Rabin </PERSON> told <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> television. `` On the contrary, today we have the methods. It will take some time but we shall succeed.'' He did not elaborate. The military commander of the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> lifted a curfew that had confined more than 120,000 <LOCATION> Nablus </LOCATION> residents to their homes since last Thursday, the army announced. It said Maj. Gen. <PERSON> Amram </PERSON> <PERSON> Mitzna </PERSON> took the action as a gesture of goodwill for the holiday of Eid al-Adha, the Moslem Feast of Sacrifice. In <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION>, 13-year-old <PERSON> Suheir </PERSON> <PERSON> Fuad </PERSON> <PERSON> Afana </PERSON> of the Beach refugee camp was critically wounded when she was hit in the stomach by army gunfire, said a <LOCATION> Shifa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION> surgeon. The girl died on the operating table, according to the doctor, who spoke on the condition he not be identified. Hospital officials said troops also shot and wounded three boys ranging in age from 11 to 15 and that all three were hit in the lower body. Army officials confirmed the death but said they were unable to determine the cause because the family took the girl's body from the hospital. They said an army unit sent to