 second round of voting is expected to last through September. <PERSON> Sarney </PERSON>, a 57-year-old provincial politician and poet from the poor northeastern state of <LOCATION> Maranhao </LOCATION>, came to power in March 1985 as the vice president for the popular statesman <PERSON> Tancredo </PERSON> <PERSON> Neves </PERSON>, who died before taking office. They were elected in indirect electoral college voting called by the military, which put <PERSON> Sarney </PERSON> on the Neves ticket. The vote was to pave the way for civilian government after 21 years of military rule.
