<DATELINE>SANTIAGO, Cuba (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 President <PERSON> Fidel </PERSON> <PERSON> Castro </PERSON> told Cubans Tuesday to prepare for the return of thousands of their soldiers from <LOCATION> Angola </LOCATION> if a peace agreement can be reached for that southern African country. In a three-hour speech marking the 35th anniversary of the launching of his leftist revolution, <PERSON> Castro </PERSON> also defended his `` rectification'' campaign for economic reform and said Soviet-style reforms are not needed in <LOCATION> Cuba </LOCATION>. He called capitalist economic policies `` complete trash.'' <PERSON> Castro </PERSON> confirmed reports that <LOCATION> Cuba </LOCATION> recently sent reinforcements to <LOCATION> Angola </LOCATION>, where it is estimated that at least 50,000 Cuban military personnel are helping the Marxist government battle rebels backed by <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. He said the reinforcements were needed to create proper conditions for a political solution in <LOCATION> Angola </LOCATION>. The governments of <LOCATION> Angola </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Cuba </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> reached an agreement this month for the removal of foreign troops from <LOCATION> Angola </LOCATION> and independence for <LOCATION> South-West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION>, the territory administered by <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION>. The <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> was represented at the talks. <LOCATION> South-West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION>, also known as <LOCATION> Namibia </LOCATION>, lies between <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Angola </LOCATION> <PERSON> Castro </PERSON> said he did not want to prejudice the continuing negotiations on <LOCATION> Angola </LOCATION> by going into detail on their status, but declared: `` We r