nnels of distribution and in all product groups,'' said <PERSON> Jon </PERSON> <PERSON> Shirley </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Microsoft </ORGANIZATION> president and chief operating officer. `` Our international operations were particularly strong, generating 47.8 percent of revenues for the year.'' For the fiscal year, net income totaled $ 123.91 million, or $ 2.22 a share, on revenues of $ 590.83 million, up from profits of $ 71.88 million, or $ 1.30 a share, on revenues of $ 345.89 million for fiscal 1987.
