<SECOND>PM-Pillsbury CEO, Bjt,0713</SECOND>
<HEAD>Can Smith Turn Pillsbury Around?</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MARIANN CAPRINO</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>'s new top executive has been criticized as lacking vital restaurant experience to turn around the company's flagging Burger King chain, but <PERSON> Philip </PERSON> <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> says he's just waiting to test his management ability. The troubled food giant on Monday plucked <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> from rival <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foods </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, where he served as chairman. The 54-year-old <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> also served as vice chairman of <ORGANIZATION> Philip </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Morris </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cos. </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, which acquired <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foods </ORGANIZATION> in 1985 He begins his new job Aug. 1. Unlike General Foods, which has rested on the success of its Oscar Mayer meats and Jell-O gelatin, <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> has few high-growth products, analysts said. `` <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> has been a big cheese in a company with a lot of easy brands,'' said <PERSON> Stephen </PERSON> <PERSON> Carnes </PERSON>, a managing director at <ORGANIZATION> Piper </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jaffray </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <LOCATION> Hopwood </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Minneapolis </LOCATION>. But at <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> `` will have to get down to trench warfare, and he was never in that mode before,'' <PERSON> Carnes </PERSON> said. Minneapolis-based <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION>, the nation's fourth-largest food conglomerate, produces <ORGANIZATION> Green </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Giant </ORGANIZATION> vegetables, Haagen-Dazs premium ice creams and <PERSON> Van </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Kamp </PERSON>'s frozen fish. Of greater concern to some is <PERSON> Smith </PERSON>'s lack of experience in the restaurant business. <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION>'s restaurant unit, which also includes Steak & amp; Ale and <PERSON> Bennigan </PERSON>'s, accounts for nearly half of the company's total revenue. In the fiscal year ended May 31, restaurant sales slipped 5 percent as <PERSON> Burger </PERSON> <PERSON> King </PERSON> continued losing market share to rival <ORGANIZATION> McDonald </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> despite a $ 200 million advertising campaign. `` <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION>'s weakness has been more related to restaurants, and if they got a guru in restaurants, they may have been better off,'' said <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Froelich </PERSON>, an analyst at <ORGANIZATION> Pershing </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co </ORGANIZATION>. Echoing those concerns, <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> stock fell $ 1.75 a share to $ 35.12 -LCB- Monday on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. But <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> is confident he can transfer his management skills to a new industry. In a telephone interview, he said: `` I feel I have a very good understanding of the operating fundamentals in the restaurant business. I'm going to have an opportunity first hand to test whether my judgments about what's important are right or not.'' <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> follows in the footsteps of the hard-charging <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> H. </PERSON> <PERSON> Spoor </PERSON>, who returned from retirement to run <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> on an acting basis nearly five months ago when former chairman <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Stafford </PERSON> resigned under pressure. Analysts have criticized <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION>, saying it lacked clear and vital leadership in recent years. Its after-tax profit plummeted 62 percent in fiscal 1988 to $ 69.3 million on sales of $ 6.2 billion, largely because of a restructuring charge associated with the sale of its Godfather's Pizza chain and a number of other restaurant operations and consolidations General Foods' performance under <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> is not immune to criticism, either, some analysts say. <PERSON> Smith </PERSON>, a 22-year veteran of General Foods, counters that between 1984 and 1987, <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foods </ORGANIZATION>' growth rate went from `` relatively flat to the point where we're growing better than 3 percent a year.'' As for management style, <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> said he typically tries to `` determine what the basic direction is we should be going and then in a very aggressive and determined kind of way provide clear direction to the organization and insist on commitment and dedication.'' Despite speculation on Wall Street, analysts are divided as to how attractive a takeover candidate <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> may be. <PERSON> Carnes </PERSON>, for instance, said <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> had `` too many wrecks in the ditch right now.'' Some experts have estimated the Burger King chain could fetch as much as $ 1.5 billion if it were spun off as a separate company, but <PERSON> Carnes </PERSON> said the chain would bring only about $ 900 million because it was at least two years away from a turnaround. <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> said he would be surprised if selling Burger King `` made any sense.'' `` It has been very successful in the past, and I have to believe there is room for a strong No. 2'' in the fast-food hamburger business, he said. <PERSON> Philip </PERSON> <PERSON> Morris </PERSON> stated that <PERSON> Smith </PERSON>'s position would not be filled. The heads of the subisidary's domestic foods, coffee and <PERSON> Oscar </PERSON> <PERSON> Mayer </PERSON> units would report directly to <PERSON> Hamish </PERSON> <PERSON> Maxwell </PERSON>, <PERSON> Philip </PERSON> <PERSON> Morris </PERSON> chairman.
</TEXT>
